> Page Object Model:

    - page object model is design pattern which is used in automation framework
      which helps to organize our code

    - in automation, if we write everything in one file, it becomes difficult to maintain

    - for example, if a locator changes, we have to update it in multiple places,
      so because of this, maintenance becomes complex

    - in page object model we will create separate classes for each page,
      and each class contains web elements and related methods

    - if i explain further:
        - yaml locator file contains all xpath locators
        - class contains action methods
        - test class contains test scenarios

    - for example, interface page:
        - all locators contains in yaml file
        - all actions methods contains in page file

        Methods:
        --------
            - page is loaded
            - filter attributes
            - create interface
            - edit interface
            - delete interface
            - get table status

    * so whenever UI changes, we update only in page file, not in all testcases
